The Enugu State Government has declared that it was not true a case of Corona Virus, also known as COVID-19, was recorded in Nsukka axis of the state. The permanent secretary of the ministry of Health in the state, of the Dranyi Agujiobi stated this in Enugu. According to him, the rumour making the rounds was “false” and “fake news’’ propelled by mischief-makers. “The Enugu State Ministry of Health wish to dispel the rumours making the rounds that there is a case of Corona Virus in Nsukka. “This is false, misleading and fake; as there is no testing centre in the whole of Enugu State. “The general public is informed that as at today, March 22, there is no case of Corona Virus in Enugu State,’’ he said. He, however, urged residents of the state to observe personal health hygiene. “Even as all is encouraged to restrict movement, cancel all unimportant gathering and to observe personal health hygiene,’’ he added.